(56, 5, 'What is the capacity of Batching Plant?', '<p>35m3/H &amp; 60 m3/H</p>\r\n', 'Batching Plant', NULL),
(57, 3, 'Q. Which system is better for me â€“ Off-Grid or On-Grid and why?', '<p>A.&nbsp;If backup is needed then it is good to go for off-grid system. If electricity bill reduction (common utility bill or daytime consumption) is needed then on-grid system is best suited.</p>\r\n', '', NULL),
(58, 3, 'Q. What are the benefits of solar? ', '<p>A. Solar energy is green and saves electricity.</p>\r\n', '', NULL),
(59, 3, 'Q. What is Net Metering?', '<p>A.&nbsp;Net metering is the aggregate metering of electricity consumption. It accounts both import and export of electricity. Net metering ensures just billing because of this factor.&nbsp; It is needed for solar systems if electricity generated from solar has the likelihood of export to national grid.</p>\r\n', '', NULL),
(60, 3, 'Q. How do I size my solar system? ', '<p>A.&nbsp;Sizing of solar system depends on a number of factors like available space, shading, requirement, utility provider&rsquo;s recommendation and purpose. We can provide expert solar solution after knowing these factors and visit.</p>\r\n', '', NULL),
(61, 3, 'Q. Iâ€™m not getting good backup from my off-grid solar system. How to fix it? ', '<p>A.&nbsp;Probably the battery(s) is(are) damaged or have poor health. Battery(s) should be replaced or maintained if under warranty.</p>\r\n', '', NULL),
(62, 3, 'Q. How will I know that my On-Grid system is supplying electricity?', '<p>A.&nbsp;There are two simple ways, either monitor energy meter readings or compare electricity bills of before and after period of solar installation.</p>\r\n', '', NULL),
(63, 3, 'Q. I have an existing non-operational solar system.  Can it be upgraded?', '<p>A.&nbsp;If the panels are not damaged, the system can be upgraded to an on-grid system. The rest of the items may need to be scrapped.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', NULL),
(64, 3, 'Q. Why will an on-grid system not function during electricity outages/night?', '<p>A.&nbsp;This is so because it run as a supplementary source over a primary source or in other words it works in parallel to grid. While running with grid, it saves daytime electricity consumption.</p>\r\n', '', NULL),
(65, 3, 'Q. How frequently batteries of an off-grid system need replacement and maintenance?', '<p>A.&nbsp;Replacement depends on use and maintenance. Usually a battery lasts for 2 years.</p>\r\n', '', NULL),
(66, 3, 'Q. Will installing solar on rooftop have any effect on my building?', '<p>A.&nbsp;Not much but needs some drilling and chipping of rooftop. Additional solar structure on rooftop has no significant effect.</p>\r\n', '', NULL),
(67, 3, 'Q. Is there any risk involved with solar installations?', '<p>A.&nbsp;No, there is no risk involved if well-maintained and well-installed</p>\r\n', '', NULL),
(68, 3, 'Q. What is a hybrid solar system?', '<p>A.&nbsp;A hybrid system is basically a mixture of an on-grid and an off-grid system. It can act like an IPS to provide electricity backup during night or outage and can supply the grid should it have surplus amount of solar energy.</p>\r\n', '', NULL),
(69, 3, 'Q. Solar systems are expensive and bad investments. Is it true? ', '<p>A.&nbsp;No, in fact solar is a good long-term investment because electricity price is ever-rising but solar installation&rsquo;s electricity price will remain the same.</p>\r\n', '', NULL),
(70, 2, 'Q. What is Blue light and how it affects vision? How will I know if my lights are emitting UV or other harmful radiation?', '<p>A.&nbsp;Blue light as its name suggest is bluish light emitted from a white light source. It has been known to cause retinal fatigues and can even cause cancer. It has also been known to cause sleep problems too. If your room lights look violet or bluish in color, they are likely to emit so. &nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', NULL),
(71, 2, 'Q. Does LED lights generate lot of heat like CFL/incandescent bulbs/halogen lights?', '<p>A.&nbsp;No. LED lights are highly energy efficient.</p>\r\n', '', NULL),
(72, 2, 'Q. What are the benefits of LED lighting? ', '<p>A.&nbsp;Customizable, long lamp life, energy saving, cooler than other lighting solutions and environment-friendly.</p>\r\n', '', NULL),
(73, 2, 'Q. How does CRI affect lighting?', '<p>A.&nbsp;Higher the CRI, the accurate is the color of objects.</p>\r\n', '', NULL),
(74, 2, 'Q. Do I need to replace/remove existing ballasts and chokes if I replace my existing lights?', '<p>A.&nbsp;Yes. LED lights don&rsquo;t need these.</p>\r\n', '', NULL),
(75, 2, 'Q. I have installed LED lights in my home/office but when I switch them on my TV/radio doesnâ€™t work properly. Why is it so?', '<p>A.&nbsp;It is likely one or several lights have low PF, high THD and are emitting unwanted electromagnetic radiation that is interfering with other electronics.</p>\r\n', '', NULL),
(76, 2, 'Q. LED lights are expensive than other lights. Why should I switch to LED lights even after this difference?', '<p>A.&nbsp;Because in long-terms, LED lights pay-off well compare to other solutions. LED lights are not hazardous and have no known health effects. LED lights are repairable and robust.</p>\r\n', '', NULL),
(77, 2, 'Q. Where to use warm lighting and cool lighting?', '<p>A.&nbsp;Warm lighting is good for decoration and spaces where reading is not done on a regular basis. Cool lighting is recommended for work places and reading areas.</p>\r\n', '', NULL),
(78, 2, 'Q. Do I need to change my existing lighting fixtures if I switch to LED lights?', '<p>A.&nbsp;Maybe you would need so for accommodation.</p>\r\n', '', NULL),
